<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keay, Bull. Jard. Bot. Etat Bruxelles 26: 193" authorityYear="1956" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Deinbollia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Deinbollia saligna" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saligna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Deinbollia saligna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on www.iucnredlist.org. It was assessed globally as Vulnerable (World Conservation Monitoring Centre, 1998). In 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
the species was assessed for the Red data Checklist of Cameroon as Vulnerable. This taxon is currently known from four localities. The extent of occurrence of the species is estimated at less than 100 km2, and the area of occupancy is about 16 km2. The localities are threatened by proposals for dam construction and timber extraction. Based on these threats, and the continuous decline of vegetation cover in the area, extent and /or quality of habitat 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. saligna" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="saligna">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. saligna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here reassessed as Endangered: IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Endangered ENB2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
